through the historical analysis of your urban evolution, your development process, and
your landfills, from the implantations of its ports. Vitória, a port city that was born and
developed along with its port, has undergone significant changes on your landscape.
This landscape, which is a reflex of a complex and symbiotic relationship between portcity,
common in port cities dynamics, can be characterized, with the necessaries
temporal adaptations, in each time period. Analyzes the port landscape transformations
using two main theoretical-methodological references: Hoyle Model (1989), that
addresses an analysis with a historical and chronological perspective the development
of port-city interface and the Landscape Analysis and Construction Method proposed by
Mendonça (2005), whose methodology proposes among others aspects, identification,
characterization and perception of main natural and constructive landscape references.
Were realized conceptual approaches about landscape and identification of methods to
be used in this study. About the empirical context, the port city relationship was
analyzed, from the historical and participatory approach, with emphasis on the
landscape transformation, examining the sources that were constituted of original
documents, academic papers, technical studies, town planning laws, photographs,
postcards and field research. To identify the elements that characterize the
contemporary port landscape, which was addressed in regional, metropolitan and
seaside metropolitan scale, a field survey was done called ?the waters? route?. In this
changing transformation, which contributes to the construction of the place collective
memory, there are losses, gains and stays with the implementation and development of
its ports. It was evidenced that Vitória, whose foundation officially refers to the year
1551, which was born squeezed between the sea and the mountains and has developed
along the wood quay and timber wharfs, with warehouses facing the bay, keeps always,
in port function, one of its main economic and cultural forces. Vitória?s port-city
relationship characterizes, either by proximity and dependency, with its quays and
timber wharfs; for expansion and development with its linear pier, sometimes by physical
separation between port and city and search for new territories in industrial landscape
and, currently, is pursuing for rapprochement. The study concluded that Vitória has
characterized in its landscapes the references marks of the port-city relationship, that
shows a temporal difference from the periodization proposed by Hoyle (1989).In this
context, seeks to draw attention to the continuing importance of the port on Vitória?s
landscape, becoming, despite the structural changes occurred over time, an relevant
